  "A study compares the lifecycle greenhouse gas emissions of electricity from different sources per kilowatt-hour. Coal produces approximately 1,000 g CO2-equivalent, natural gas produces about 500 g, solar produces about 50 g, and wind produces about 15 g. However, natural gas advocates argue that gas is a 'clean fuel.' Why is this claim misleading?": "",
