  "Natural gas has zero emissions when burned, as most introductory frameworks would predict when analyzing produces dynamics": "",
  "Calling natural gas 'clean' is relative only to coal; it still emits roughly 500 g CO2-eq/kWh compared to 15-50 g for wind and solar, and methane leakage during production can add 25-50% more climate impact, making it incompatible with deep decarbonization goals.": "",
  "Communities in the coal mining regions of West Virginia and Kentucky have experienced decades of health problems including higher rates of cancer, lung disease, and heart disease compared to national averages. Researchers attribute this to coal dust exposure, contaminated water from mining, and poverty. What concept does this pattern exemplify?": "",
