  "This pattern illustrates environmental injustice: communities that host fossil fuel extraction often bear disproportionate health and environmental burdens while receiving limited economic benefits, and these communities are frequently low-income and have less political power to resist harmful practices.": "",
  "OPEC (Organization of the Petroleum Exporting Countries) controls approximately 40% of global oil production and holds about 80% of proven reserves. When OPEC restricts production, global oil prices rise, affecting transportation costs, food prices, and economic growth worldwide. What geopolitical concept does this illustrate?": "",
